HEADWORD: Marish
<hw>Mar"ish</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧r"⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>marais</ets>, LL. <ets>marascus</ets>. See <er>Marsh</er>.]</ety>
<def>Low, wet ground; a marsh; a fen; a bog; a moor.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au> <au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
